SIMPLE: princess
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Princess
<hw>Prin"cess</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>princesse</ets>. See <er>Prince</er>, and cf.
<er>Princesse</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A female prince; a woman
having sovereign power, or the rank of a prince.</def>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So excellent a <qex>princess</qex> as the present queen.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The daughter of a sovereign; a female member of a
royal family.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The consort of a prince; <as>as, the
<ex>princess</ex> of Wales</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Princess royal</b></col>, <cd>the eldest daughter of a
sovereign.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Princesse</ent>⟦br⟧
